Re the tagging, I have been thinking about this one, the only passive tag I can think of for now is some sort of passive radar reflector built into the lander structure. <br>
<br>
Advantages;<br>
<br>
uses no power so could function even if the lander is damaged (may even work if it is destroyed as long as it is not too badly destroyed! IYSWIM).<br>
<br>
Disadvantages;<br>
<br>
Adds weight, Needs an active and fairly sensitive radar system on the orbiter (but then most missions these days seem to have some sort of radar mapping)<br>
