<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 0] --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/alien.gif ALT="0]"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
Kucinich authored and introduced the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.fas.org/sgp/congress/2001/hr2977.html">Space Preservation Act of 2001</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. This delighted conspiracy theorists by providing &quot;breakthrough&quot; credibility to such concepts as mind-control beams, &quot;chemtrails&quot; and &quot;extra-terrestrial weapons&quot;. <br>
<br>
It was later re-written to eliminate some of the wackier references, naturally causing the conspira-loons to make dark inferences about suppression and censorship.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
<br>
SEC. 7. DEFINITIONS.<br>
<br>
In this Act:<br>
<br>
(1) The term `space' means all space extending upward from an altitude greater than 60 kilometers above the surface of the earth and any celestial body in such space.<br>
<br>
(2)(A) The terms `weapon' and `weapons system' mean a device capable of any of the following:<br>
<br>
(i) Damaging or destroying an object (whether in outer space, in the atmosphere, or on earth) by--<br>
<br>
(I) firing one or more projectiles to collide with that object;<br>
<br>
(II) detonating one or more explosive devices in close proximity to that object;<br>
<br>
(III) directing a source of energy (including molecular or atomic energy, subatomic particle beams, electromagnetic radiation, plasma, or extremely low frequency (ELF) or ultra low frequency (ULF) energy radiation) against that object; or<br>
<br>
(IV) any other unacknowledged or as yet undeveloped means.<br>
<br>
(ii) Inflicting death or injury on, or damaging or destroying, a person (or the biological life, bodily health, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>mental health,</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> or physical and economic well-being of a person)--<br>
<br>
(I) through the use of any of the means described in clause (i) or subparagraph (B);<br>
<br>
(II) through the use of land-based, sea-based, or space-based systems using radiation, electromagnetic, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>psychotronic</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, sonic, laser, or other energies directed at individual persons or targeted populations for the purpose of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>information war, mood management, or mind control</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of such persons or populations; or<br>
<br>
(III) by expelling chemical or biological agents in the vicinity of a person.<br>
<br>
(B) Such terms include exotic weapons systems such as--<br>
<br>
(i) electronic, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>psychotronic, or information</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> weapons;<br>
<br>
(ii) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>chemtrails;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
(iii) high altitude ultra low frequency weapons systems;<br>
<br>
(iv) plasma, electromagnetic, sonic, or ultrasonic weapons;<br>
<br>
(v) laser weapons systems;<br>
<br>
(vi) strategic, theater, tactical, or <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>extraterrestrial</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> weapons; and<br>
<br>
(vii) chemical, biological, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>environmental, climate, or tectonic weapons.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
(C) The term `exotic weapons systems' includes <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>weapons designed to damage space or natural ecosystems (such as the ionosphere and upper atmosphere) or climate, weather, and tectonic systems</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> with the purpose of inducing damage or destruction upon a target population or region on earth or in space.<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>(emphasis added)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=atomicconspiracy>Atomic Conspiracy</A> at: 1/6/04 2:47 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yales>yales</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1394<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/6/04 2:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=990.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~yales/images/53invad2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ok, I apologize for the slur against Martians</span><hr size=1> I think the proposal is quite reasonable.<br>
<br>
Kuchinich is proposing that weapons not be proliferated into space - both those in usage now, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>forestalling</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;exotic&quot; capabilities not yet in production.<br>
<br>
The items highlighted in the text above - such as psychotronic and information warfare (apparently as examples of being loony) are precisely the potentials which are under development or consideration.<br>
<br>
Some examples:<br>
<br>
From: <br>
<br>
=========================================<br>
PARAMETERS - US Army War College Quarterly <br>
The United States Army's Senior Professional Journal<br>
Spring 1998<br>
<br>
&quot;The Mind Has No Firewall&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://carlisle-www.army.mil/usawc/Parameters/98spring/thomas.htm">carlisle-www.army.mil/usawc/Parameters/98spring/thomas.htm</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
=============================================<br>
<br>
Here is a sampling from:<br>
<br>
AU/ACSC/279/1998-04<br>
AIR COMMAND AND STAFF COLLEGE<br>
AIR UNIVERSITY<br>
...<br>
Appendix A<br>
The Inventory<br>
<br>
Infrasound/VLF Very low frequency, high intensity sound.<br>
-- Disorients and frightens. Interferes with organ functions, causing nausea and bowel spasms.<br>
<br>
Neural Inhibitors<br>
-- Incapacitates personnel, paralyzing synaptic pathways.<br>
<br>
Pulsed High Power Microwaves (HPM)<br>
-- Induces confusion, stupor or coma in personnel and animals.<br>
<br>
==========================================<br>
<br>
The phrase &quot;extra-terrestrial weapons&quot; was emphasized. Why? It is EXACTLY the correct term:<br>
<br>
===================================<br>
The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language: Fourth Edition.  2000.<br>
<br>
extraterrestrial <br>
  <br>
ADJECTIVE: Originating, located, or occurring outside Earth or its atmosphere<br>
=====================================<br>
<br>
In other words: orbiting laser weapons, kinetic kill vehicles, electromagnetic pulse generators, atomic directed beam weapons, etc. <br>
The phrase means exactly what the topic of the bill was concerning. <br>
<br>
<br>
Note also Kuchinich's use of the term &quot;exotic&quot;. He does not specify the existence or non-existence of those systems. He specifically states (in the unposted part of his bill) that the purpose is to PREVENT research and development of these potential (or actual) systems BEFORE they are problems.<br>
<br>
yale <br>
